## Intended Shape

This blueprint is for a **service-oriented Python backend** where FastAPI is the real application framework, not just a generic REST placeholder. Use it when the project needs:

- request/response models with strong schema validation
- async-first HTTP handlers
- a clear boundary between API, services, repositories, and background work
- explicit operational guidance for auth, migrations, and testing

## Quick Start

{% if package_manager == "uv" %}
```bash
uv venv
source .venv/bin/activate
uv sync
uv run alembic upgrade head
uv run uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000
```
{% elif package_manager == "poetry" %}
```bash
poetry install
poetry run alembic upgrade head
poetry run uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000
```
{% else %}
```bash
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements-dev.txt
alembic upgrade head
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000
```
{% endif %}

