## Operational Guidance

{% if auth_strategy == "jwt" %}
- Use stateless JWT auth for machine-friendly and SPA-friendly flows.
- Keep token verification in `app/core/security.py`; do not spread it across routers.
{% elif auth_strategy == "oauth2" %}
- Use OAuth2 flows for delegated auth and external identity providers.
- Treat callback handling and token exchange as infrastructure concerns, not business logic.
{% elif auth_strategy == "api-key" %}
- Use hashed API keys for programmatic consumers.
- Store only key digests, never plaintext values.
{% else %}
- No authentication is scaffolded. Confirm this is acceptable before production work starts.
{% endif %}

{% if use_background_jobs %}
- Reserve `app/workers/` for Celery, Arq, RQ, or similar job handlers.
- Route handlers should enqueue long-running work instead of blocking request threads.
{% endif %}

{% if use_redis %}
- Redis is assumed for short-lived cache/session/queue coordination, not as the system of record.
{% endif %}

